&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;the best of both worlds&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;the best of both worlds&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to enjoy the advantages of two very different things at the same time. (दोनों दुनिया का सबसे अच्छा)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; By working part-time, she gets the best of both worlds - time with her kids and a career.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The context tells us that she can benefit from these quite distinct things at the same time because she lives in a rural region with access to the metropolis.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

