	&lt;li&gt;An &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Iconoclast&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is a person who attacks cherished beliefs or institutions.(वह व्यक्ति जो पारंपरिक धारणाओं या प्रथाओं का विरोध करता है )&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;correct answer&lt;/strong&gt; is: &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Iconoclast&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impregnable:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Impossible to capture, break into, or overcome; unable to be conquered or defeated. (दुर्गम)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Immoral&lt;/strong&gt;: Contrary to accepted moral principles or standards; unethical; morally wrong. (अनैतिक)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Insolvent&lt;/strong&gt;: Unable to pay debts or meet financial obligations; bankrupt. (दिवालिया)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 2&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;i.e.&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;No error&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;Your ears are itching because you are having an allergic reaction.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;grammatically correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; This sentence is clear and concise.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It adheres&lt;/strong&gt; to the standard English grammar rules and it has a clear subject &amp;quot;Your ears&amp;quot;, verb &amp;quot;are itching&amp;quot; and it is connected with another clause &amp;quot;because you are having an allergic reaction&amp;quot; that explains why the subject is in the state that it is.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This&lt;strong&gt; sentence follows &lt;/strong&gt;the subject-verb-object (SVO) word order and every segment of it is correct with no errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt; is:&lt;em&gt; &amp;#39;Your ears are itching because you are having an allergic reaction.&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Voyage&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The word that can substitute the given sentence is &amp;quot;Voyage&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s understand the meaning of the given words&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Voyage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;: A long journey, especially by sea or in space.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: &lt;/em&gt;The ship&amp;#39;s voyage took three months to cross the Atlantic.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Sojourn:&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;A temporary stay in a place, a short period of time spent in a place.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt; He made a sojourn in the city before continuing his journey.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Elegy:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; A poem or song written in memory of someone who has died, especially one that expresses sorrow or mourning.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt; He wrote an elegy for his late wife.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Safari: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;A journey or expedition, especially in Africa, for hunting, exploration, or scientific research.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt; The family went on safari to see the wildlife in the savanna.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is important to note that &amp;quot;voyage&amp;quot; is a long journey, &amp;quot;sojourn&amp;quot; is a short stay, &amp;quot;elegy&amp;quot; is a poem or song written to mourn someone who passed away, and &amp;quot;safari&amp;quot; usually refers to a journey or expedition in Africa for hunting, exploration or scientific research.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct answer: &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Voyage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;are&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The subject of the sentence is &amp;quot;Child prodigies,&amp;quot; which is plural.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Since the sentence is in the present tense, the correct auxiliary verb should also be in the present tense.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Are&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is the correct present tense form that agrees with the plural subject.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options (&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;is&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;was&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;were&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;) do not correctly match the subject-verb agreement in the present tense.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;remarkable&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the impact of child prodigies on societal development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The appropriate adjective should describe significant or noteworthy changes in society.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Remarkable&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; fits well as it conveys the idea of extraordinary or significant changes brought by child prodigies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options (&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;forgotten&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;ordinary&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;professional&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;) do not align with the context of highlighting exceptional societal changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Nonetheless&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the reality of child prodigies and how they are perceived versus the actual impact they make in history.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence before the blank mentions that these children thrive everywhere, their parents are happy, and their peers envy them.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Nonetheless&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; fits well here as it introduces a contrast, indicating that despite these positive perceptions, research shows they rarely change history.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options (&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;So that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Which&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Neither&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;) do not fit logically in the context.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;notable&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the achievements of historical figures in contrast to child prodigies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The appropriate word should describe figures who had a significant impact on history.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Notable&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; fits well as it refers to people who are remarkable or worthy of attention.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options (&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;researcher&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;dumb&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;lame&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;) do not fit the context of describing historically significant individuals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Researcher (अन्वेषक): &amp;quot;Researcher&amp;quot; refers to someone conducting studies or investigations, which does not fit the context.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Dumb (मूर्ख): &amp;quot;Dumb&amp;quot; means lacking intelligence, which is the opposite of the intended meaning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Lame (कमजोर): &amp;quot;Lame&amp;quot; means weak or unconvincing, which does not describe historical figures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;a whimper&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The phrase &amp;ldquo;not with a bang, but a whimper&amp;rdquo; originates from TS Eliot&amp;rsquo;s poem &amp;quot;The Hollow Men&amp;quot; and is commonly used to describe an anticlimactic or quiet ending.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In the context of the passage, it implies that while child prodigies show early promise, their impact on history tends to fade rather than culminate in something grand.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;A whimper&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; fits best as it conveys the idea of an underwhelming or unremarkable conclusion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options do not fit the idiomatic phrase or the intended meaning of the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;An impalpable&amp;quot; (अस्पृश्य) means something that cannot be touched or grasped, which does not fit in the context of describing an ending.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;A reconcile&amp;quot; (समाधान) is grammatically incorrect and does not fit the context.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;An indomitable&amp;quot; (अजय) means impossible to subdue, which contradicts the idea of fading away quietly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

