&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The passage flows logically from identifying an initial issue with the Hubble Space Telescope (Q), sending missions to repair and address this issue (P), and upgrading its systems for better functionality (R), leading to the improvement mentioned in S1 and S6.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Q identifies the specific initial problem encountered by the Hubble Space Telescope which directly relates to the subject introduced in S1, making it the natural starting point for the middle sentences.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;P logically follows as it talks about the action taken to correct the initial issue identified in Q.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;R expands on the repair missions by mentioning the upgrades made, which is a continuation of the action mentioned in P but with a forward-looking outcome.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;S reveals the result of these repairs and upgrades, leading directly into S6, which talks about the expanded understanding of the universe thanks to Hubble&amp;#39;s improved capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &amp;lsquo;Option 2&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/strong&gt;

